This paper discusses the reproducibility of deep reinforcement learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on evaluating and comparing different RL algorithms. The second most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), as the paper specifically evaluates RL algorithms on real-world robots. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as RL is a sub-field of AI. The fourth likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as some RL algorithms are used for vision-based tasks. The fifth likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as RL is used for control tasks in robotics and other systems.
